{
  "texts": [
    "It employs scale-wise dense connections and backward fusion to enhance multi-scale feature integration, followed by refinement for high-quality image reconstruction.",
    "Notably, SRUNet omits pooling layers, typically used in U-Net, to prevent information loss, crucial due to the small datasets characteristic of hyperspectral imaging.",
    "An initial preprocessing convolutional layer addresses noisy inputs, with MAE serving as the loss function, tailored for the precise demands of hyperspectral image reconstruction.",
    "These data-driven methods showcase the versatility of machine learning and statistical approaches in hyperspectral image reconstruction, enabling the extraction of meaningful infor-1 3 mation from complex hyperspectral datasets.",
    "The choice of method often depends on the specific goals of the reconstruction task and the characteristics of the hyperspectral data being analyzed"
  ]
}